dcterms:description: The LOOP-SEA dataset is collected by inductive loop detectors deployed on 4 connected freeways in the greater Seattle area, containing traffic speed data of 323 sensor stations over the whole year of 2015 with a time interval of 5 minutes.
dcterms:title: LOOP-SEA Dataset

dcterms:description: The PEMS-BAY dataset is collected by California Transportation Agencies and contains speed information of 325 sensor stations in the Bay Area, covering six months from January 1st, 2017 to June 30th, 2017 with a time interval of 5 minutes.
dcterms:title: PEMS-BAY Dataset
